abstract: The European Union hopes to de-escalate trade tensions with the United States but wants Washington to lower steel tariffs or make another goodwill gesture after a series of concessions by Brussels in recent years, a top EU lawmaker said Thursday.
snippet: The European Union hopes to de-escalate trade tensions with the United States but wants Washington to lower steel tariffs or make another goodwill gesture after a series of concessions by Brussels in recent years, a top EU lawmaker said Thursday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The European Union hopes to de-escalate trade tensions with the United States but wants Washington to lower steel tariffs or make another goodwill gesture after a series of concessions by Brussels in recent years, a top EU lawmaker said Thursday.
headline_main: Europe Looking for Positive Signal From U.S. on Trade: EU Lawmaker
headline_print_headline: Europe Looking for Positive Signal From U.S. on Trade: EU Lawmaker

abstract: The former New York City mayor laid out his views on the scope and limits of presidential authority and potential post-Trump curbs.
snippet: The former New York City mayor laid out his views on the scope and limits of presidential authority and potential post-Trump curbs.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — If Michael R. Bloomberg is elected president, he says he would be “extremely reluctant” to order the military to attack another country without congressional authorization or an imminent threat to the United States. But he left himself wiggle room, stopping short of saying it would be unconstitutional for him to use force without lawmakers’ approval in other situations.

abstract: If the virus spreads in the United States, the Federal Reserve might have to cut rates. But how fiscal policymakers respond is likely to be even more important.
snippet: If the virus spreads in the United States, the Federal Reserve might have to cut rates. But how fiscal policymakers respond is likely to be even more important.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The global spread of the deadly coronavirus is posing a significant economic test for President Trump, whose three-year stretch of robust growth could be shaken by supply chain delays, a tourism slowdown and ruptures in other critical sectors of the American economy.

abstract: Kentucky Gov. Andy Beshear defended a photograph of him posing with drag queens at a gay rights rally and accused a Republican lawmaker of using homophobic tactics by displaying the photo at a recent campaign rally while accusing Democrats of corrupting traditional values.

abstract: Democratic White House hopefuls are seizing on President Donald Trump’s delayed response to the coronavirus outbreak, calling it the latest evidence of his incompetence and warning that the crisis may only deepen as a result.
snippet: Democratic White House hopefuls are seizing on President Donald Trump’s delayed response to the coronavirus outbreak, calling it the latest evidence of his incompetence and warning that the crisis may only deepen as a result.
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, S.C. — Democratic White House hopefuls are seizing on President Donald Trump’s delayed response to the coronavirus outbreak, calling it the latest evidence of his incompetence and warning that the crisis may only deepen as a result.
headline_main: White House Hopefuls Target Trump on Coronavirus Response
headline_print_headline: White House Hopefuls Target Trump on Coronavirus Response

abstract: Frustrated Democrats again lambasted Senate Republican leader Mitch McConnell Thursday as they marked a year of Senate inaction since the House passed landmark gun control legislation.
snippet: Frustrated Democrats again lambasted Senate Republican leader Mitch McConnell Thursday as they marked a year of Senate inaction since the House passed landmark gun control legislation.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Frustrated Democrats again lambasted Senate Republican leader Mitch McConnell Thursday as they marked a year of Senate inaction since the House passed landmark gun control legislation.
headline_main: A Year After House Vote, Dems Challenge McConnell on Guns
headline_print_headline: A Year After House Vote, Dems Challenge McConnell on Guns

abstract: Rebekah Mercer, whose family foundation was a major Trump donor, stepped down from the museum when her term expired in December.
snippet: Rebekah Mercer, whose family foundation was a major Trump donor, stepped down from the museum when her term expired in December.
lead_paragraph: Rebekah Mercer, an influential donor to conservative causes — including groups that deny climate science — has quietly stepped down from the American Museum of Natural History, one of the country’s most prominent science museums.

abstract: The Senate has passed a bill to provide $1 billion for small telecom providers to replace equipment made by China's Huawei and ZTE, sending the measure to President Donald Trump.
snippet: The Senate has passed a bill to provide $1 billion for small telecom providers to replace equipment made by China's Huawei and ZTE, sending the measure to President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The Senate has passed a bill to provide $1 billion for small telecom providers to replace equipment made by China's Huawei and ZTE, sending the measure to President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Bill to Help Small Telecoms Excise Huawei Goes to Trump
headline_print_headline: Bill to Help Small Telecoms Excise Huawei Goes to Trump

abstract: The Democratic nomination could be wrapped up next month. That is too soon to select any candidate.
snippet: The Democratic nomination could be wrapped up next month. That is too soon to select any candidate.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic Party has created a dramatically front-loaded primary schedule this year, with the intention of wrapping up the nomination quickly. Party leaders had hoped that a shortened campaign would produce a nominee with plenty of time and resources to mount a strong challenge against Donald Trump. Those Democrats tired of long campaigns were pleased.
